BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-07T163352.072.png
CATEGORIES:Talks,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260409T064135Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a conversation with Arundhati Roy that engages with her literary and political writing\, tracing the intersections of fiction\, memory\, and contemporary realities. The discussion will focus on her book\, 'Mother Mary Comes to Me'\, situating the text within Roy’s broader body of work and her sustained engagement with questions of identity\, dissent\, and narrative form.\n\nModerated by Nandini Nair\, the session will reflect on the movement between the personal and the political in Roy’s writing\, and consider how storytelling can shape and respond to public discourse.\n\n&nbsp\;\n\nPlease note that registration does not guarantee a seat\; it is on a first-come\, first-serve basis. 
DTEND:20260416T140000Z
DTSTART:20260416T123000Z
SUMMARY:Writing in the Present: Arundhati Roy in Conversation with Nandini Nair
UID:1245@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/writing-in-the-present-arundhati-roy-in-conversation-with-nandini-nair/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-02T115627.608.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260408T044226Z
DESCRIPTION:This is a hand-stitching workshop guided by artist afra eisma and Karin Iturralde Nurnberg—at the heart of which is the idea of emotional repair.\n\nPatches mend and reinforce worn garments\, they can also represent healing\, protection\, and strength. Drawing on the theme of the warrior garments\, participants are encouraged to reflect on their own experiences and emotions\, translating them into stitched forms. Through this process\, making patches become more than decoration or repair\; they become a way of reclaiming\, protecting\, and reimagining parts of oneself. 
DTEND:20260411T113000Z
DTSTART:20260411T083000Z
SUMMARY:Mend and Make
UID:1242@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/mend-and-make/
END:VEVENT
