DESCRIPTION:A series of faculty-led sessions in the form of talks\, lectures or workshops are delivered by faculty members of Srishti Manipal Institute of Art\, Design &amp\; Technology. These sessions range from sounds\, urban biodiversity\, metaphor-making\, livelihoods\, ecosystems and more.\n\nSchedule\nApril 7\nOn Seeing the Sound in a Changing Environment by Dr Guruaja\, K. V.\n\nApril 18\nWhere Have all the Sparrows Gone? by Aparna Raman\n\nApril 21\nSlow Disturbances by Priya Joseph\n\nApril 25\nClimate Metaphors by Asmita Sarkar\n\nMay 5\nThe Ghosts of Conservation by Rustam Vania\n\nMay 9\nClimate Canvases by Dr Chandrima Home and Dr Sambita Modak\n\nPlease note: Each session requires individual registration. Some sessions require you to bring certain materials so please be prepared.
SUMMARY:Learning Lounge
UID:1238@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/learning-lounge/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-08T095613.041.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260409T054111Z
DESCRIPTION:Image credit: A still from the video "Skin of Things 2025” by Asmita Sarkar\n\nMetaphors are more than ornaments of language. They shape our thoughts and help us find meaning and beauty\, by bringing into being new ways of seeing and articulating experience. The point of departure for this workshop is a few art-science explorations by artist and researcher Asmita Sarkar\, who has worked with sleep researchers at NCBS\, Bangalore. The exploration of circadian\, diurnal\, and circannual rhythms helps create metaphors that connect the molecular to the cosmic levels\, illustrating how various climate events influence human and non-human bodies. \n\nWorkshop participants will create their own climate change metaphors. Thus\, creating meaning out of different facets of a messy\, nebulous problem\, which apparently has no simple resolution.
DTEND:20260425T070000Z
DTSTART:20260425T050000Z
SUMMARY:Climate Metaphors
UID:1247@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/climate-metaphors/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-07T103045.923.png
CATEGORIES:Exhibition Opening,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260409T042835Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the preview of warrior garments-afra eisma followed by an intimate performance by Aanchal Bordoloi and refreshments by Chef Tresa Francis from Coracle.\n\nStitched\, layered\, painted and charged with feeling\, Dutch artist afra eisma’s warrior garments  invite you into a world where anger is not contained\, but worn. afra's practice is colourful and playful\, yet quietly carries weight. Their work asks us to think about what it means to feel safe in all your vulnerabilities.\n\nAt MAP\, we believe safe spaces belong to everyone. Keeping in line with this ethos\, for the first time we are inviting all our audiences to be a part of the opening night of this exhibition. Join us afra for a guided walk of the exhibition\, followed by an intimate live performance by Aanchal Bordoloi.\n\nDrawing on years of original songwriting and the tradition of storytelling in close\, connected spaces\, Aanchal invites you into a conversation between artist and listener\, leaving you with something to carry home long after the evening ends.\n\nWe look forward to welcoming you for this special evening.
DTEND:20260410T153000Z
DTSTART:20260410T123000Z
SUMMARY:Preview Night: warrior garments
UID:1244@map-india.org
